--create a new dir 
--vagrant commit -m
--nano the vagrant config file

as a test example you could put:


Vagrant.configure("2") do |config|
  config.vm.provider "docker" do |d|
    d.image = "ghost"
  end  
end


d.image should be a valid example 


once done 

--vagrant up :  this will start the image
--vagrant halt :  to stop the contaner
--vagrant status  : this should give the status of the all the containers that you have start with vagrantfile
--vagrant destroy -f  : this should destroy the container


